# 🗳️ Presidential Election Visualization

R code for analyzing and visualizing U.S. Presidential Election results through choropleth maps and static graphics. This project explores how electoral data can be transformed into informative visuals.

## Overview

Focuses making election data legible and readable. 

## Features

- **Data wrangling pipeline** — Raw election data cleaned, reshaped, and joined with geographic data for analysis
- **Choropleth mapping** — State and/or county-level election results rendered as color-scaled geographic maps
- **Static export-ready graphics** — Clean, publication-quality visuals suitable for reports or presentations

## Tech Stack

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| R | Core analysis and visualization |
| ggplot2 | Charting and map rendering |
| tidyverse | Data cleaning and transformation |
| sf / maps | Geospatial data handling |

## Getting Started

```r
# Clone the repo, then install dependencies
install.packages(c("tidyverse", "ggplot2", "sf"))

# Run the main visualization script
source("main.R")
```

## Data Sources
https://electionlab.mit.edu/

## About

Built as part of a personal data visualization portfolio. Feedback and contributions welcome.
